if not entirely pure.

19:34.716 --> 19:37.851
She came in here and propositioned me!

19:37.919 --> 19:39.453
Exposed herself to me, like a whore.

19:39.520 --> 19:40.921
I see through your game.

19:40.988 --> 19:42.088
You're trying

19:42.156 --> 19:43.924
to drive me from my position,

19:43.991 --> 19:45.759
so you can take over.

19:45.827 --> 19:48.262
First the newspaper...

19:48.329 --> 19:50.698
and now, lipstick?

19:52.668 --> 19:55.036
But it's not gonna work
because you don't know

19:55.104 --> 19:57.239
what you think you know.

19:57.307 --> 20:01.110
You're coming apart
at the seams, Sister.

20:01.178 --> 20:04.547
Perhaps it would be best
if you took a leave of absence.

20:07.717 --> 20:08.617
(quiet laugh)

20:09.886 --> 20:12.720
I'm on to you.

20:17.259 --> 20:19.427
Blessed are thee,
blessed are thou among women...

20:19.494 --> 20:22.630
(phone ringing)

20:30.672 --> 20:34.040
Briarcliff Manor.

20:34.108 --> 20:36.743
Hello?

20:36.811 --> 20:40.513
Hello?
Who is this?

20:40.581 --> 20:43.049
GIRL:
You left me there.

20:46.887 --> 20:49.322
Who...

20:49.390 --> 20:53.226
who is this?

20:53.294 --> 20:56.129
You never even bothered
to get out of the car.

20:57.965 --> 20:59.933
(sobbing)

21:08.109 --> 21:11.045
I'm sorry.

21:11.112 --> 21:12.413
I'm so sorry.

21:12.480 --> 21:15.249
(click, dial tone drones)

21:21.924 --> 21:24.192
(sobbing)

21:24.260 --> 21:25.827
No... (sobs)

22:17.989 --> 22:19.690
(thunder crashes)

22:33.940 --> 22:35.207
ANNOUNCER:
Travel warnings continue

22:35.275 --> 22:37.276
for Freemont and Braintree Counties.

22:37.344 --> 22:39.545
Flooding expected in Miranda
and parts of Cape Cod.

22:39.612 --> 22:41.747
Stay indoors.

22:41.815 --> 22:43.349
We have more on those strange
lights sighted

22:43.416 --> 22:45.284
over parts of Wasagee County.

22:45.352 --> 22:46.685
Residents continue to insist

22:46.753 --> 22:48.321
these are not lightning strikes.

22:48.388 --> 22:51.423
Fears of a possible downed
aircraft have put

22:51.491 --> 22:53.525
local emergency
rescue workers on the alert.

22:53.593 --> 22:56.929
So far, the cause of the strange
activity remains a mystery.

22:58.531 --> 23:01.400
(patients clamoring)

23:10.776 --> 23:12.210
(blows whistle)

23:18.552 --> 23:20.753
Take your seats!

23:20.821 --> 23:23.556
Take your seats!
No more dillydallying!

23:23.624 --> 23:24.324
Sit down!

23:26.127 --> 23:27.160
Sit down!

23:31.232 --> 23:32.532
Is everyone accounted for?

23:32.600 --> 23:33.800
The Mexican wasn't in

23:33.868 --> 23:36.269
her room, so I was
gonna go look for her.

23:36.336 --> 23:38.171
No, I want you to stay here.

23:38.239 --> 23:41.674
I'll go, after
I introduce the picture.

23:41.742 --> 23:43.109
Okey-doke.

23:46.947 --> 23:49.182
Welcome, one and all,

23:49.250 --> 23:53.453
to Briarcliff Manor's
inaugural movie night.

23:53.520 --> 23:55.321
(chuckles)

23:55.389 --> 24:00.661
Whether this evening marks the
start of a, of a beloved trend,

24:00.728 --> 24:07.335
tradition, or just another
bitter disappointment,

24:07.402 --> 24:09.504
is entirely up to you.

24:13.442 --> 24:16.644
Now...

24:16.712 --> 24:21.282
settle in, relax,
and return with me now

24:21.350 --> 24:24.319
to ancient Rome as we present

24:24.387 --> 24:30.925
the 1932
Cecil B. DeMille classic,

24:30.993 --> 24:33.161
<i>The Sign of the Cross,</i>

24:33.228 --> 24:39.267
starring Miss Claudette Colbert
as the Empress Poppea...

24:39.335 --> 24:40.969
or "Po-ppea,"

24:41.037 --> 24:44.206
and as the Emperor Nero,

24:44.274 --> 24:49.344
the incomparable
Mr. Charles Laughton...

24:49.412 --> 24:51.880
who I understand
is an enormous whoopsie.

24:51.948 --> 24:53.715
(thunder crashes, patients scream)

24:53.783 --> 24:56.318
Now none of that!
None of that! None of that.

24:56.386 --> 24:57.919
Chin up! Chin up high! Hey!

25:01.691 --> 25:03.993
Now don't be afraid of the dark.

25:07.363 --> 25:10.499
At the end...

25:10.566 --> 25:13.302
of a storm...

25:13.369 --> 25:14.670
is a golden sky...

25:14.738 --> 25:19.508
the bright silver song...

25:19.575 --> 25:21.509
of a lark.

25:21.577 --> 25:25.546
Walk on through the wind.

25:25.614 --> 25:28.216
Walk on through the rain.

25:28.283 --> 25:30.952
(chuckles)

25:31.020 --> 25:35.157
Though your dreams may be tossed
and blown...

25:35.225 --> 25:40.229
walk on, walk on...

25:40.297 --> 25:43.867
with hope...

25:43.935 --> 25:45.402
in your heart.

25:49.141 --> 25:50.441
And you'll never walk alone.

25:50.509 --> 25:52.843
You'll never walk a...

25:52.911 --> 25:54.912
But she was alone.

25:58.117 --> 26:03.255
A tiny, little fragile
thing out, out in the world,

26:03.322 --> 26:06.391
in the gloaming.

26:06.458 --> 26:10.328
And the storm that came...

26:10.395 --> 26:16.167
was not rain and it was not wind.

26:16.235 --> 26:20.438
It was something...

26:20.506 --> 26:22.140
altogether else.

26:24.543 --> 26:26.310
(gasps)

26:27.913 --> 26:29.113
(thunder crashes, patients clamor)

26:35.487 --> 26:36.754
Lights.

26:36.822 --> 26:38.823
I'm off to find the Mexican.

26:48.133 --> 26:50.267
What the hell was that all about?

26:50.335 --> 26:52.269
LANA: She's bats,
or hadn't you noticed?

26:52.337 --> 26:54.271
MAN (in film):
Burn, Rome, burn!

26:54.339 --> 26:57.975
(laughing)

26:58.043 --> 27:00.344
Did you speak to Wendy?
What?

27:00.411 --> 27:03.647
I tried to phone you,
but there was no answer.

27:03.715 --> 27:05.149
So I went to check on her.

27:05.217 --> 27:06.951
(door creaks)

27:07.019 --> 27:08.819
Hello?

27:08.887 --> 27:10.621
<i>I rang the bell,</i>
<i>but the door was unlocked,</i>

27:10.689 --> 27:11.856
<i>so I let myself in.</i>

27:18.697 --> 27:20.197
(door creaks)

27:22.034 --> 27:23.867
Hello? Is anyone here?

27:25.470 --> 27:27.171
Miss Peyser?

27:31.476 --> 27:32.943
Wendy?

27:33.011 --> 27:34.845
(wind whistling)

27:37.848 --> 27:40.917
Miss Winters, I know how
alarming this is, but I'm afraid

27:40.985 --> 27:42.419
something might have
happened to your friend.

27:42.487 --> 27:44.654
What do you mean?

27:44.722 --> 27:48.191
(wind whistling)

27:48.259 --> 27:52.061
THREDSON:
<i>There were certain similarities</i>

27:52.129 --> 27:54.029
<i>between Miss Peyser's disappearance</i>

27:54.065 --> 27:56.065
<i>Shh!</i>
<i>and some of the other victims.</i>

27:58.201 --> 27:59.768
Shh!
Other victims?

27:59.836 --> 28:01.870
What are you saying?

28:01.938 --> 28:03.438
MAN (in film):
Yes, Divine Caesar, these rumors

28:03.506 --> 28:07.141
about my setting fire to the city...

28:07.208 --> 28:09.576
That I have some...
Shh!

28:09.644 --> 28:12.079
Shh!

28:12.147 --> 28:15.449
Couldn't we shift the blame to...?

28:15.517 --> 28:18.052
The Christian?

28:18.119 --> 28:19.720
(man yelling)

28:19.788 --> 28:21.588
(film continues indistinctly)

28:26.394 --> 28:28.629
That I have some concerns,

28:28.697 --> 28:30.398
concerns which I've
related to the police.

28:30.465 --> 28:33.701
But unfortunately, they're
so invested in the idea

28:33.769 --> 28:35.102
that they've already
caught their maniac

28:35.170 --> 28:37.604
that they won't even
entertain the idea.

28:37.672 --> 28:40.440
But maybe they haven't.

28:40.508 --> 28:42.509
(man yelling)
Sit down and watch the movie!

28:42.577 --> 28:45.245
Hey, Bernie?

28:47.548 --> 28:49.916
(yelling continues)

28:49.984 --> 28:52.718
But they have caught him,
haven't they?

28:52.786 --> 28:56.521
Do you think I could use
the bathroom really quickly?

28:56.589 --> 28:58.223
What is it with you people?

28:59.392 --> 29:00.692
Haven't they?

29:00.760 --> 29:05.763
To be honest, I'm not so sure anymore.

29:05.831 --> 29:08.533
I'm having my period.
Ah, I don't want to hear it.

29:08.600 --> 29:10.201
Don't make me come with you, okay?

29:10.269 --> 29:12.303
Yeah. Thank you.

29:15.374 --> 29:17.776
WOMAN (in film):
Which perfume, Empress?

29:17.843 --> 29:20.312
EMPRESS:
The jasmine and the acacia.

29:20.379 --> 29:24.783
(various patients wolf whistling)

29:24.851 --> 29:28.920
There are so many beautiful
women in Rome.

29:28.988 --> 29:31.656
It's really not appropriate
for me to be seeing this...

29:31.724 --> 29:34.225
considering my condition.
Sister Jude will understand.

29:34.293 --> 29:36.561
I'm going to the ladies'.

29:36.628 --> 29:39.330
POPPEA: Dacia, you're a butterfly
with the sting of a wasp.

29:39.398 --> 29:40.798
Take off your clothes.

29:40.866 --> 29:45.002
Get in here and tell me all about it.

29:45.070 --> 29:47.571
Hello?

29:47.639 --> 29:49.140
(thunder crashes)

29:55.647 --> 29:57.080
Where's that goddamn Mexican?

29:57.148 --> 29:58.882
(distant clank)

30:03.522 --> 30:05.657
Who's there?

30:10.829 --> 30:12.062
Who's there?

30:20.904 --> 30:23.239
We picked a hell of a night for it.

30:23.307 --> 30:24.774
Yeah, it's good.
Perfect, in fact.

30:24.841 --> 30:26.809
The storm will cover our tracks.

30:26.876 --> 30:29.378
All we have to do is
go through those doors,

30:29.445 --> 30:31.680
through the staff lounge
and into the boiler room.

30:31.747 --> 30:32.948
And that'll take us where, Narnia?

30:33.015 --> 30:35.150
There's an old tunnel

30:35.218 --> 30:37.318
that leads into the woods--
assuming it's really there.

30:37.386 --> 30:40.055
It's there. That touched nun
brought me through it.

30:40.122 --> 30:42.557
I'll show you;
just take me with you.

30:42.625 --> 30:46.494
Screw you.
You had your chance.

30:46.562 --> 30:49.064
I was wrong about you.
I'm sorry.

30:49.132 --> 30:50.799
But someone I love may be in danger.

30:50.867 --> 30:53.168
I know you can understand that.

30:53.236 --> 30:54.269
GRACE:
We have to take her down.

30:54.337 --> 30:55.904
She'll raise the alarm.

30:55.972 --> 30:57.639
No, she won't.
She's coming with us.

30:57.707 --> 30:59.074
GRACE:
What?!

30:59.142 --> 31:00.375
We don't have time to argue.
Come on.

31:02.512 --> 31:03.913
Shit.

31:03.980 --> 31:06.048
Carl's out there.
What are we gonna do?

31:06.116 --> 31:07.116
Whatever we have to.

31:07.184 --> 31:08.485
We may not get another chance.

31:08.552 --> 31:09.719
We're going through that door.

31:09.787 --> 31:11.288
You're not taking down Carl.

31:11.355 --> 31:14.191
He was a Marine.
He fought in Korea.

31:14.259 --> 31:16.693
I'll make sure
you get through the door.

31:16.761 --> 31:19.096
Just, just try and wait for me.
Wait for you?

31:19.164 --> 31:21.431
If you can't, if I don't make it out,

31:21.499 --> 31:24.301
make sure you write the story

31:24.368 --> 31:26.002
that blows the doors off this place.

31:26.070 --> 31:27.804
Don't forget about me.

31:30.341 --> 31:32.676
Shelley, what are you doing out here?

31:32.744 --> 31:34.812
I got bored.
Yeah, you're always bored.

31:34.879 --> 31:38.015
You need to be in that movie
with the others. Go on.

31:38.082 --> 31:39.349
I've already seen it.

31:39.417 --> 31:41.151
The Christians get eaten.

31:41.219 --> 31:43.420
I'd rather be eating something else.

31:43.488 --> 31:45.622
Shelley, I don't have time.

31:45.690 --> 31:46.923
The Mexican's missing.

31:46.991 --> 31:48.925
Jude's out here looking, too.

31:48.993 --> 31:50.227
Did you check the hydrotherapy room?
What?

31:50.295 --> 31:53.197
Come on, Carl...
I'll help you look.

31:53.265 --> 31:55.133
You never know where
she might be hiding.

31:57.069 --> 31:58.770
Shit, Shelley.

31:59.973 --> 32:01.841
Come on.

32:07.516 --> 32:09.583
Stop!

32:10.819 --> 32:13.287
Damn it, I said stop!

32:27.834 --> 32:29.835
There you are...

32:29.903 --> 32:31.704
whore.

32:39.813 --> 32:40.546
(groans)

32:47.388 --> 32:49.322
I don't see a door.
It's here.

32:52.760 --> 32:54.328
Come on.

33:04.006 --> 33:05.172
Whore.

33:07.043 --> 33:07.876
Whore...

33:14.350 --> 33:15.517
Whore!

33:20.156 --> 33:22.024
(moaning)

33:24.028 --> 33:25.695
Hey, why'd you stop?

33:27.798 --> 33:29.432
I'm sorry, Carl.

33:29.500 --> 33:31.334
I gotta get out of here.

33:31.402 --> 33:34.170
(screams, gasps)

33:34.237 --> 33:36.172
(thunder crashing)

33:39.709 --> 33:41.042
Where do you think you're going...

33:43.946 --> 33:45.280
...whore?

33:54.222 --> 33:55.956
(rattling in distance)

33:58.794 --> 34:00.160
(door clanks, screeches open)

34:00.228 --> 34:01.428
(thunder rumbling)

34:01.496 --> 34:03.263
We waited as long as we can.

34:03.331 --> 34:05.032
Something must have happened to her.

34:05.100 --> 34:06.366
Any minute now, they're gonna
notice we're missing

34:06.434 --> 34:07.768
from that movie,
if they haven't already.

34:07.835 --> 34:09.703
We'll get her out.
Her and everybody else.

34:09.771 --> 34:11.638
I'll expose every
sick thing going on here.

34:17.978 --> 34:18.911
Let's go.

34:18.980 --> 34:20.781
(thunder crashing)

34:25.987 --> 34:27.789
(whooping, laughing)

34:30.626 --> 34:33.360
I didn't think I could feel
this good ever again,

34:33.429 --> 34:34.594
and I hate the rain.

34:37.132 --> 34:39.132
(thunder crashing)

34:39.201 --> 34:40.301
Come on, we have to get
as far away from here,

34:40.369 --> 34:42.103
while we still can.

34:42.170 --> 34:43.670
From what I remember,

34:43.737 --> 34:44.605
the road's a couple miles
north of here.

34:44.672 --> 34:46.306
That way, through the trees.

34:46.375 --> 34:48.141
I don't trust you.
Once we get to the road,

34:48.210 --> 34:49.476
that's as far as you go with us.

34:52.614 --> 34:55.650
(anxious whimpering)

34:55.717 --> 34:57.551
(hissing)

34:57.619 --> 35:00.120
(woman screaming in film)

35:02.891 --> 35:05.392
It's our time!
It's our time!

35:05.459 --> 35:07.393
We're not afraid.

35:07.461 --> 35:09.595
MAN (in film): Stand up there!
(whip cracks)

35:09.663 --> 35:12.032
WOMAN (in film):
Go proudly! Singing!

35:12.099 --> 35:15.736
There is no death, only
a crossing over to the Father.

35:15.803 --> 35:19.039
(lions growling in film)

35:20.141 --> 35:21.875
Excuse me.
What?

35:21.943 --> 35:23.510
There appear to be
some patients missing.

35:23.578 --> 35:24.578
Have you been aware of that?

35:27.815 --> 35:28.749
Oh, shit.

35:28.816 --> 35:30.150
Pepper pee.

35:30.218 --> 35:32.286
Yeah, go on. Go pee.

35:32.354 --> 35:35.322
(Christian martyrs singing in film)

35:38.293 --> 35:39.360
Excuse me, Sister.

35:39.428 --> 35:40.761
I think we might have a problem.

35:40.829 --> 35:42.463
Now?

35:42.531 --> 35:45.333
But the Christians are
about to be eaten.

35:45.401 --> 35:46.601
(thunder crashing)

35:50.172 --> 35:52.007
(singing continues in film)

35:57.080 --> 35:58.380
(thunder crashes)

35:58.448 --> 36:00.149
I was just going to the infirmary.

36:00.216 --> 36:00.783
(lock clicks)

36:03.920 --> 36:05.287
I think I'm going to vomit.
That's fine.

36:07.157 --> 36:08.524
Go ahead.

36:08.592 --> 36:09.692
We can play doctor right here.

36:09.760 --> 36:11.794
No, I'm not in the mood.

36:11.861 --> 36:12.828
(chuckles)

36:12.896 --> 36:14.630
You're always in the mood.

36:14.698 --> 36:17.499
I must be the only guy in
here who hasn't had you yet.

36:17.567 --> 36:19.401
That's not true.

36:19.469 --> 36:21.604
What's more, I'm the one
who does the choosing.

36:21.671 --> 36:23.406
Not tonight.

36:23.473 --> 36:26.776
Turn around... and
spread your cheeks.

36:26.843 --> 36:29.912
I thought I repulsed you.
Any port in a storm.

36:29.980 --> 36:30.813
Now bend over!
(yells)

36:30.881 --> 36:32.715
(thunder crashes)

36:32.783 --> 36:34.150
I don't want to.

36:34.218 --> 36:35.485
I want to go back to the movie.

36:35.553 --> 36:36.420
(with mock sympathy):
Oh...

36:38.056 --> 36:39.189
(Shelley yells)

36:39.257 --> 36:42.192
No...! No!

36:42.259 --> 36:44.661
No! Help!

36:44.728 --> 36:46.929
Rape!

36:46.997 --> 36:47.997
(scoffing): Rape.
Help!

36:48.065 --> 36:50.332
That's rich, coming from you.

36:50.399 --> 36:52.200
(screams)
Go ahead, scream your head off.

36:52.268 --> 36:53.835
No one's going to hear you in here.

36:53.903 --> 36:55.336
Help!

36:57.606 --> 37:00.641
(laughing, then muffled snickering)

37:00.709 --> 37:02.476
Don't you dare laugh at me.

37:04.112 --> 37:05.446
(laughing):
What happened?

37:05.514 --> 37:06.414
Shut up!

37:06.482 --> 37:08.449
Were you in an accident?

37:08.517 --> 37:10.952
Oh, you're seven feet all,
I thought you'd be hung like...

37:11.019 --> 37:11.752
Shut up!
(thud)

37:14.355 --> 37:15.956
(thunder crashing)

37:18.993 --> 37:19.826
(screams)

37:22.597 --> 37:24.298
(screams)

37:24.365 --> 37:26.133
I think we found the Mexican!

37:26.201 --> 37:28.602
(eerie growling in distance)

37:38.481 --> 37:40.182
KIT: Run!
(screaming)

37:47.791 --> 37:50.126
What are they?
What's chasing us!

37:50.194 --> 37:51.594
(screaming)

37:51.662 --> 37:52.595
KIT: Don't look back!
Just run!

37:52.663 --> 37:54.764
(screeching)

37:54.831 --> 37:56.165
(growls)

37:56.233 --> 37:57.066
Come on!

37:58.635 --> 38:00.303
KIT: Go! Run, run!
Into the tunnel!

38:12.882 --> 38:14.416
(door clanks shut)

38:14.483 --> 38:18.019
(knocking on door)
Sister Jude? Sister Jude?

38:18.087 --> 38:20.488
Sister...

38:20.556 --> 38:21.556
you need to wake up.

38:25.595 --> 38:27.597
What's going on?
Frank said I had to fetch you.

38:27.664 --> 38:29.232
There's a big problem.
They're very worried.

38:29.299 --> 38:31.434
Oh, my God in Heaven.

38:31.502 --> 38:32.802
They've seen it, too.

38:32.870 --> 38:35.338
Seen what, Sister?

38:38.009 --> 38:39.042
What...?

38:44.282 --> 38:47.418
Please explain to me
how three patients

38:47.485 --> 38:50.655
could just get up and walk out
of here right under your nose.

38:50.722 --> 38:53.124
I guess I was just watching the movie.
Yeah.

38:53.191 --> 38:56.227
(crowd yelling in movie)

38:56.294 --> 38:58.396
MAN (in movie):
...renounced his faith.

38:58.463 --> 39:00.464
Movie night is at an end.

39:00.532 --> 39:02.566
(audience protesting)
But the picture's not over.

39:02.634 --> 39:04.702
Yeah, well, they all die.
Satisfied?

39:04.770 --> 39:06.304
Now, listen up.

39:06.371 --> 39:09.006
There will not be another movie night

39:09.074 --> 39:11.242
nor any other special privileges

39:11.309 --> 39:13.077
in the foreseeable future.

39:13.144 --> 39:16.881
And for that, you can thank
the three scofflaws

39:16.948 --> 39:18.849
who abused my good will.

39:18.917 --> 39:21.385
(thunder crashes)

39:23.288 --> 39:27.157
A sex-crazed deviant, a Mexican,

39:27.225 --> 39:30.994
and a pinhead won't get far
in this storm.

39:31.062 --> 39:32.596
I hope they all drown out there.

39:32.664 --> 39:34.931
Lights out in ten minutes.

39:34.999 --> 39:37.000
All right, let's go.

39:39.403 --> 39:41.305
(raspy breathing)

39:44.509 --> 39:45.342
(groans)

39:49.514 --> 39:50.547
(gasping)

39:50.615 --> 39:52.849
SHELLEY:
Please...

39:52.917 --> 39:54.351
let me go.

39:58.023 --> 39:59.890
Sister Jude will look for me.

39:59.958 --> 40:01.225
Oh, they are looking for you.

40:01.293 --> 40:04.795
In the woods.

40:04.863 --> 40:06.997
You see, they all think
you ran away last night,

40:07.065 --> 40:09.767
along with several of the others.

40:09.835 --> 40:14.739
In fact, Sister Jude thinks
you're the ringleader.

40:14.807 --> 40:16.441
(anxious gasping)

40:16.508 --> 40:18.643
Please...

40:18.711 --> 40:21.179
if you let me walk out of here,

40:21.246 --> 40:22.580
I won't tell them anything.

40:22.648 --> 40:24.449
I promise!

40:24.516 --> 40:25.683
I'm afraid that's quite impossible.

40:25.751 --> 40:27.986
You were a very
naughty girl last night.

40:28.053 --> 40:31.422
You tried to fly away,
so I had to clip your wings.

40:31.490 --> 40:32.924
But not to worry.

40:32.992 --> 40:35.293
My surgical training was impeccable.

40:38.364 --> 40:39.364
(gasps)

